 Extended Tower Number Field Sieve: A New Complexity for Medium Prime Case
 Taechan Kim
Abstract: In this paper, we extend the tower number field sieve~(TNFS) proposed by Barbulescu, Gaudry, and Kleinjung in Asaicrypt 2015. Our generalization based on the JLSV algorithm (by Joux, Lercier, Smart, and Vercautern, Crypto 2006) shows that one can solve the discrete logarithm over the field $\F_Q := \F_{p^n}$ in time complexity, L_Q( 1/3, (64/9)^{1/3} ), for p = L_Q( \ell_p) with some \ell_p > 1/3.
